### Foreign Objects in Your Food: A Grim Reality

Today's digest shines a spotlight on the risks lurking in our food supply, with recent recalls from notable brands due to foreign object contamination. Ajinomoto Foods North America Inc. tops the list with a disturbing series of incidents involving glass fragments in their frozen prepared foods. Several products, including their Green Gyoza Vegetable & Edamame Dumplings and Ling Ling Restaurant Style Fried Rice, have been recalled over concerns of glass pieces ranging from 1-3 cm in size. This issue was also found in their Tai Pei Shrimp Fried Rice and Trader Joe's Vegetable Fried Rice offerings.

Another concerning recall involves Mangalm LLC's mustard oil-based pickles, which have been flagged for potential adulteration with erucic acid, a compound that can pose health risks when consumed in excessive quantities.

### The Scoring Tales of Woes

When examining the recall patterns across the food industry, certain brands stand out for all the wrong reasons. Moonlight Packing Corporation and Albertsons Companies LLC lead this ignoble category with the highest number of Class I recalls this year, making them risk-heavy choices for consumers. Ajinomoto Foods North America Inc., already under scrutiny for glass contamination, also ranks among the top due to its repeated violations. It's a stark reminder that being a big name doesn't always guarantee safety.

### A Year in Reflection

So far this year, the USDA's recall statistics paint a grim picture. With 286 total recalls in 2026, including 83 Class I recalls--the most severe category--it's evident that the industry still faces systemic issues. Foreign object contamination accounts for 78 recalls, while allergens remain the leading cause with 170 incidents. This is a call to action for manufacturers to tighten quality controls and ensure safe production practices.

### Our Verdict

Given the frequency of these issues, it's imperative for consumers to stay informed about food recalls and avoid complacency. Brands like Ajinomoto Foods North America Inc. and Albertsons Companies LLC need to address their quality assurance processes to prevent recurring problems. Food safety is not merely a regulatory requirement but a fundamental necessity for public trust and health.
